'''''From The Doctor to my son Thomas''''' is a [[viral video]] recorded by actor [[Peter Capaldi]] and sent to [[autism|autistic]] nine-year-old Thomas Goodall to console him over grief from the death of his grandmother. Capaldi filmed the video [[wiktionary:in character|in character]] as the [[Twelfth Doctor|twelfth incarnation]] of [[Doctor (Doctor Who)|the Doctor]] in the [[BBC]] science-fiction series ''[[Doctor Who]]''. Capaldi's message had a positive impact on Thomas; his father stated the boy smiled for the first time since learning of his grandmother's death and gained the courage to go to her funeral. Thomas's father Ross Goodall posted the video to [[YouTube]] on 6 November 2014. He explained to media that he wanted to make the video available to his family and had no idea it would become popular to the wider public on the Internet.

[[CNN]] reported that after its appearance on YouTube, the video garnered over 200,000 views in its first 48-hour period of availability.<ref name="grinberg" /> [[BBC News]] noted that by the next day it had received greater than 500,000 views.<ref name="bbccomforts" /> By 11 November 2014 it had over 900,000 total views.<ref name="washingtonpost" /> BBC News observed that Capaldi's message had become a viral video.<ref name="bbccomforts" /><ref name="bbcmundo" /> ''[[ITV News]]'' described response to the video as [[Internet phenomenon|global phenomenon]].<ref name="worldwidephenomenon" />

''[[The Guardian]]'' called the recording by Capaldi, "a heartwarming video message".<ref name="rawlinson" /> CNN characterized the video similarly,<ref name="grinberg" /> as did other publications in [[Spanish language|Spanish]],<ref name="lavanguardia" /><Ref name="bbcmundo" /> and [[Dutch language|Dutch]].<ref name="deredactie" /> ''[[The Independent]]'' wrote that Capaldi "showed his softer side" by sending the message.<ref name="selby" /> ''[[MTV]]'' called Capaldi "a super awesome human being".<ref name="mtv" /> ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' described the video as a "touching message" to a "grieving boy".<ref name="alicevincent" /> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' observed that as his character the Doctor, Capaldi was "doing what he can to lift spirits".<ref name="hollywoodreporter" /> ''[[Hollywood Life]]'' admitted: "We shed a bunch of happy tears after listening to that message."<Ref name="hollywoodlife" /> ''[[International Business Times]]'' reported: "It was a short and simple message, but one that has had a profound impact on the little boy."<ref name="ibt" /> ''[[BT Group|BT]]'' commented of Capaldi's contribution: "this unique performance may well be his most admirable adventure yet."<Ref name="btgroup" />

==Background==
[[File:Peter Capaldi 2009 (cropped).jpg|thumb|[[Peter Capaldi]] in 2009]]
Scottish actor and film director [[Peter Capaldi]] was cast in 2013 as the [[Twelfth Doctor|twelfth incarnation]] of [[Doctor (Doctor Who)|the Doctor]] in the BBC science-fiction series ''[[Doctor Who]]''. His casting was announced on 4 August 2013 in a special BBC programme hosted by [[Zo<U+00EB> Ball]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-23570354 |title=Doctor Who: Peter Capaldi revealed as 12th Doctor|work=[[BBC News]]|date=4 August 2013|accessdate=10 November 2014|publisher=BBC|archivedate=27 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427073433/http://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-23570354}}</ref> Capaldi first appeared as the Doctor in a cameo in the 50th anniversary special, "[[The Day of the Doctor]]", before appearing in the 2013 Christmas special, "[[The Time of the Doctor]]". A lifelong fan of the series, Capaldi had previously played Lobus Caecilius in the 2008 episode "[[The Fires of Pompeii]]" as well as playing civil servant [[John Frobisher]] in the 2009 spin-off ''[[Torchwood: Children of Earth]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Doctor Who sets the controls for Rome, AD 79|work=[[What's on TV]]|date=25 September 2007|publisher=Time, Inc|url=http://www.whatsontv.co.uk/doctor-who/news/doctor-who-sets-the-controls-for-rome-ad-79|accessdate=10 November 2014|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110190412/http://www.whatsontv.co.uk/doctor-who/news/doctor-who-sets-the-controls-for-rome-ad-79}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=BBC|work=[[BBC|BBC Press Office]]|title= Filming under way for new series of Torchwood|url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/pressreleases/stories/2008/08_august/26/torchwood.shtml|date= 26 August 2008|accessdate= 10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121112194227/http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/pressreleases/stories/2008/08_august/26/torchwood.shtml|archivedate=12 November 2012}}</ref>

Before taking the role, Capaldi stated that he had to seriously consider the increased level of visibility that would come with the part.<ref>{{cite news|title=Doctor Who: Peter Capaldi promises 'no flirting' with sidekick in new series|url=http://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2014/jul/27/peter-capaldi-doctor-who-no-flirting-sidekick-coleman-new-series|accessdate=10 November 2014|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=27 July 2014|accessdate=10 November 2014|archivedate=28 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140828193914/http://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2014/jul/27/peter-capaldi-doctor-who-no-flirting-sidekick-coleman-new-series}}</ref> He revealed in an interview with ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' that he had been invited to audition for the role of the [[Eighth Doctor]] in 1995 prior to the production of [[Doctor Who (film)|the 1996 TV film]] but didn't go, stating: "I didn't go. I loved the show so much, and I didn't think I would get it, and I didn't want to just be part of a big cull of actors."<ref>{{cite news|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=1 August 2014|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20741515_20839792_2,00.html|accessdate=10 November 2014|title=Once Upon a Time Lord|first=Clark|last=Collis|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110192116/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20741515_20839792_2,00.html}}</ref>

==Prior correspondence==
Thomas Goodall was a devoted fan of ''Doctor Who'' from [[North Baddesley]], [[England]] since the age of two, and penned a letter to Peter Capaldi stating he hoped the actor found success portraying the character of The Doctor in his newly cast role.<ref name="grinberg" /><ref name="rawlinson">{{Cite news|first=Kevin|last=Rawlinson|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=10 November 2014|date=9 November 2014|url=http://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2014/nov/10/peter-capaldi-doctor-who-video-autistic-boy|title=Doctor Who<U+2019>s Peter Capaldi sends video message to bereaved autistic boy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110193000/http://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2014/nov/10/peter-capaldi-doctor-who-video-autistic-boy|archivedate=10 November 2014}}</ref> The Goodall family were all fans of ''Doctor Who'', describing themselves as [[Whovian]]s.<ref name="romseyadvertiser" /> Thomas decorated his home with objects related to the television series.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lacasadeel.net/2014/11/el-duodecimo-doctor-ayuda-un-nino-autista-fan-de-doctor.html|accessdate=14 November 2014|language=[[Spanish language|Spanish]]|title=El Duod<U+00E9>cimo Doctor ayuda a un ni<U+00F1>o autista fan de <U+2018>Doctor Who<U+2019>|work=La Casa de El|first=Javier |last=Gonz<U+00E1>lez de la Huebra|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> Capaldi wrote back to Thomas in gratitude for the boy's well-wishes, and additionally sent a note to the child's father stating his intentions to send a video message.<ref name="rawlinson" /> Capaldi enclosed guidance to Ross Goodall on how to organize a tour of the production studios for ''Doctor Who''.<ref name="rawlinson" /> 

Ross Goodall subsequently communicated with Capaldi by getting in touch with the actor's agent, to inform him that Thomas's grandmother had died.<ref name="grinberg" /> Helen, aged 72, died in early October 2014.<ref name="romseyadvertiser">{{cite news|location=[[Romsey]], [[England]]|work=[[Romsey Advertiser]]|accessdate=14 November 2014|archivedate=14 November 2014|url=http://www.romseyadvertiser.co.uk/news/11602371.Doctor_makes_it_all_better/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141114194135/http://www.romseyadvertiser.co.uk/news/11602371.Doctor_makes_it_all_better/|title=Doctor makes it all better|date=14 November 2014}}</ref><ref name="bbcmundo">{{cite news|work=[[BBC Mundo]]|title=El video que el actor de Doctor Who le envi<U+00F3> a un ni<U+00F1>o autista para reconfortarlo|date=10 November 2014|language=[[Spanish language|Spanish]]|publisher=BBC|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/mundo/video_fotos/2014/11/141110_video_dr_who_capaldi_nino_autista_nc|accessdate=11 November 2014|archivedate=11 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111172018/http://www.bbc.co.uk/mundo/video_fotos/2014/11/141110_video_dr_who_capaldi_nino_autista_nc|quote=El video, publicado por Ross Goodall en YouTube el 6 de octubre, se volvi<U+00F3> viral.}}</ref><ref name="deredactie">{{cite news|work=Deredactie.be|title=Doctor Who: 'Ik wil dat je weet dat wij ook aan je kant staan'|language=[[Dutch language|Dutch]]|location=[[Belgium]]|date=9 November 2014|accessdate=11 November 2014|url=http://deredactie.be/cm/vrtnieuws/ookdatnog/1.2143671|archivedate=11 November 2014|first=Alexander |last=Verstraete|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111172716/http://deredactie.be/cm/vrtnieuws/ookdatnog/1.2143671}}</ref>

He told Capaldi that his son was not dealing well with the grief from his grandmother's death.<ref name="grinberg" /><ref name="washingtonpost" /> The subsequent video message to Thomas from Capaldi was received by the family three-weeks after the death of the child's grandmother.<ref name="rawlinson" />

==Video message==
{{quote box2 |width=25em | bgcolor=#c6dbf7 |align=right |halig=left | salign=right|quote="And you should know that we're on your side too."|source=&nbsp;<U+2014>[[Peter Capaldi]] as [[Doctor (Doctor Who)|the Doctor]].<ref name="rawlinson" />}}

Capaldi appears [[wiktionary:in character|in character]] as the Doctor and addresses Thomas directly, stating: "Thomas, hello!"<ref name="ibt">{{cite news|work=[[International Business Times]]|first=Anne|last=Lu|title='Doctor Who' Star Peter Capaldi Sends Touching Video to Autistic Boy, 9, Who Lost His Grandma [VIDEO]|date=10 November 2014|accessdate=10 November 2014|url=http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/572246/20141110/doctor-who-peter-capaldi-video-thomas-autistic.htm|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110211306/http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/572246/20141110/doctor-who-peter-capaldi-video-thomas-autistic.htm}}</ref><ref name="finbow">{{Cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/celebrity/s7/doctor-who/news/a609072/peter-capaldi-sends-heartfelt-video-to-autistic-doctor-who-fan.html#~oVfhiqaOaXPdjW|accessdate=10 November 2014|work=[[Digital Spy]]|first=Katy|last=Finbow|date=10 November 2014|title=Peter Capaldi sends heartfelt video to autistic Doctor Who fan|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110202405/http://www.digitalspy.com/celebrity/s7/doctor-who/news/a609072/peter-capaldi-sends-heartfelt-video-to-autistic-doctor-who-fan.html#~oVfhWMkktMxZIL}}</ref><ref name="rawlinson" /> He states his gratitude at receiving the child's letter: "Thank you very much for your letter. I really enjoyed getting it."<ref name="finbow" /><ref name="rawlinson" /><ref name="scottishdailyrecord" />

He then goes on to speak to Thomas about grief, while referencing the Doctor's adventures with [[Companion (Doctor Who)|traveling companion]] [[Clara Oswald]] (portrayed by actress [[Jenna Coleman]]).<Ref name="alicevincent" /> He tells Thomas: "Because you see, when Clara and I are travelling around in time and space, sometimes bad things happen to us. And you know what, Thomas? Sometimes sad things happen to us too. So, it<U+2019>s nice to know that there's somebody like you out there who's on our side. And you should know that we're on your side too."<Ref name="mtv" /><ref name="finbow" /><ref name="rawlinson" />

Capaldi concludes the video message by wishing Thomas to experience joy: "So you look after yourself, and take care, and be happy. Bye!"<Ref name="ibt" /><ref name="finbow" /><ref name="rawlinson" /> The video is 42 seconds in length.<ref name="dailymail">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2826637/Just-doctor-ordered-Peter-Capaldi-sends-heartwarming-video-nine-year-old-autistic-fan-help-cope-death-grandmother.html|accessdate=10 November 2014|date=8 November 2014|work=[[Daily Mail]]|title=Just what the doctor ordered: Peter Capaldi sends heartwarming video to nine-year-old autistic fan to help him cope with death of his grandmother|first=Jennifer|last=Smith|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110212259/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2826637/Just-doctor-ordered-Peter-Capaldi-sends-heartwarming-video-nine-year-old-autistic-fan-help-cope-death-grandmother.html}}</ref><ref name="gloucester">{{cite news|url=http://www.gloucestercitizen.co.uk/Doctor-star-Peter-Capaldi-sends-heartwarming/story-24475446-detail/story.html|accessdate=10 November 2014|archivedate=10 November 2014|work=[[Gloucester Citizen]]|title=Doctor Who star Peter Capaldi sends heartwarming message to grieving autistic nine-year-old boy|author=The Citizen staff|date=8 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110220127/http://www.gloucestercitizen.co.uk/Doctor-star-Peter-Capaldi-sends-heartwarming/story-24475446-detail/story.html}}</ref><ref name="washingtonpost" />

==Impact==
[[File:WPDW.png|thumb|The boy referred to in the video by Capaldi was a devoted fan of the BBC television series ''[[Doctor Who]]''.<ref name="hollywoodreporter" /><ref name="grinberg" /><ref name="washingtonpost" />]]
The family received the video from Capaldi on 3 November 2014.<ref name="hollywoodreporter" /><ref name="grinberg" /> After viewing the video, Thomas felt encouraged to attend the [[funeral]] of his grandmother.<ref name="rawlinson" /> In an interview with ''The Guardian'', Ross Goodall explained: "When he said 'sometimes sad things happen', it was as though he was mentioning it (the bereavement) without mentioning it."<ref name="rawlinson" /> He discussed the manner in which Thomas perceived emotions: "Thomas only sees black and white <U+2013> there is no grey area <U+2013> and he has taken it to mean that you can be happy, even though sad things happen."<ref name="rawlinson" /> Ross Goodall told ''The Guardian'' that prior to viewing the video from Capaldi his son did not want to attend his grandmother's funeral.<ref name="rawlinson" /> 

The boy's mother said that the video had positively impacted him and "it helped him to deal with his grief in a profound way".<ref name="radiotimes">{{cite news|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2014-11-07/peter-capaldi-sends-heartwarming-video-message-to-grieving-9-year-old-boy|accessdate=10 November 2014|work=[[Radio Times]]|title=Peter Capaldi sends heartwarming video message to grieving 9-year-old boy|author=Radio Times staff|date=7 November 2014|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110213946/http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2014-11-07/peter-capaldi-sends-heartwarming-video-message-to-grieving-9-year-old-boy}}</ref><ref name="selby" /> After watching Capaldi's message to him, Ross Goodall stated, "He was a different child."<ref name="rawlinson" /> This change included the ability to comfort his sister and step out of his day-to-day behavior patterns.<ref name="rawlinson" /> Ross Goodall said after watching the video his son smiled for the first time since his grandmother died.<ref name="grinberg" /><ref name="rawlinson" /> The family framed the letter from Capaldi that came before the video message, and Ross Goodall said Thomas looks upon it when he feels distraught.<ref name="rawlinson" />

==Posted to YouTube==
Ross Goodall uploaded the message from Capaldi to the video-sharing website [[YouTube]] on 6 November 2014.<Ref name="alicevincent">{{cite news|first=Alice|last=Vincent|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|title=Peter Capaldi's touching message to grieving boy|date=9 November 2014|accessdate=10 November 2014|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/doctor-who/11218033/Peter-Capaldis-message-to-grieving-boy.html|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110204058/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/doctor-who/11218033/Peter-Capaldis-message-to-grieving-boy.html}}</ref><ref name="grinberg" /><ref name="rawlinson" /> He made the video available on YouTube so that other members of his family could view Capaldi's message to his son.<ref name="grinberg" />

He posted in a follow-up comment on the video's location on YouTube that he was surprised at the response it had gotten online: "Wow. Had no idea this would go viral. We only posted it so family could see it after the funeral."<ref name="selby" /> He made a similar statement on [[Twitter]].<ref name="mashable">{{cite news|url=http://mashable.com/2014/11/09/peter-capaldi-doctor-who-boy-autism-video/|accessdate=10 November 2014|work=[[Mashable]]|title='Doctor Who' star helps 9-year-old boy with autism through a tough time|date=9 November 2014|first=Brian|last=Koerber|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110220553/http://mashable.com/2014/11/09/peter-capaldi-doctor-who-boy-autism-video/}}</ref> He told BBC News that he had only uploaded the video to YouTube so that his aunt and uncle would be able to watch Capaldi's message to Thomas.<ref name="bbccomforts" /> 

Thomas's father wrote: "Made such a huge difference and helped him cope with the hardest of days. It was an incredibly kind thing to do that has help Thomas gain perspective and not feel so alone in his grief. Where Thomas is autistic, he doesn't feel emotions the same way the rest of us do so this has been incredibly hard for him. This message seems to have given him the strength to keep going, with his chin up."<ref name="selby" /><ref name="mtv" /><ref name="scottishdailyrecord">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/entertainment/celebrity/watch-doctor-who-star-peter-4602247|accessdate=10 November 2014|work=[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Scottish Daily Record]]|title=Watch Doctor Who star Peter Capaldi's heartwarming video message to autistic boy following death of his gran|first=Mark|last=McGivern|date=10 November 2014|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110205902/http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/entertainment/celebrity/watch-doctor-who-star-peter-4602247}}</ref>

By 10 November 2014, total comments by viewers posted below the video on YouTube numbered in the hundreds.<ref>{{cite news|via=[[Westlaw]]|title=Time Lord takes some time out to comfort a troubled fan|work=[[The Independent]]|date=10 November 2014|first=William|last=McIennan|publisher=Independent News and Media Limited|page=14}}</ref> The majority of comments were supportive.<ref name="ibt" /> Visitors to the site wrote favorably of Capaldi's actions to record the video for the child.<ref name="ibt" /> A few observed that Capaldi's version of the Doctor character is sinister and serious, and contrasted this with the actor's depiction of the character as warm and effusive in his recording.<ref name="ibt" />

==Reception==
{{quote box2 |width=25em | bgcolor=#c6dbf7 |align=right |halig=left | salign=right|quote="this unique performance may well be his most admirable adventure yet."|source=&nbsp;<U+2014>''[[BT Group|BT]]''<ref name="btgroup" />}}

[[CNN]] reported that subsequent to its appearance on YouTube, the video garnered over 200,000 views in its first 48-hour period of availability.<ref name="grinberg">{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/11/08/showbiz/peter-capaldi-video/|work=[[CNN]]|accessdate=10 November 2014|date=8 November 2014|first=Emanuella|last=Grinberg|title='Doctor Who' Peter Capaldi sends heartwarming message to grieving fan|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110195420/http://www.cnn.com/2014/11/08/showbiz/peter-capaldi-video/|archivedate=10 November 2014}}</ref> [[BBC News]] noted that by the next day, it had received over 500,000 views.<ref name="bbccomforts">{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-hampshire-29976527|work=[[BBC News]]|date=9 November 2014|accessdate=10 November 2014|title=Doctor Who actor Peter Capaldi comforts bereaved boy|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110201717/http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-hampshire-29976527|quote=A video in which Doctor Who star Peter Capaldi comforts a bereaved nine-year-old boy with autism has gone viral on YouTube.}}</ref> By 10 November 2014 it had over 750,000 total views.<ref name="dailyecho">{{cite news|accessdate=10 November 2014|date=10 November 2014|url=http://www.dailyecho.co.uk/news/11590842.Doctor_Who_s_heart_warming_message_to_boy_for_gran_s_funeral/|work=[[Southern Daily Echo]]|title=The Doctor Peter Capaldi sends video to nine-year-old Thomas Goodall ahead of his grandmother's funeral|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110223025/http://www.dailyecho.co.uk/news/11590842.Doctor_Who_s_heart_warming_message_to_boy_for_gran_s_funeral/}}</ref><Ref name="hampshirechronicle">{{cite news|url=http://www.hampshirechronicle.co.uk/leisure/leisure_news/11590842.Doctor_Who_sends_video_message_to_boy_for_gran_s_funeral/|accessdate=10 November 2014|title=The Doctor Peter Capaldi sends video to nine-year-old Thomas Goodall ahead of his grandmother's funeral|work=[[Hampshire Chronicle]]|date=10 November 2014|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110221125/http://www.hampshirechronicle.co.uk/leisure/leisure_news/11590842.Doctor_Who_sends_video_message_to_boy_for_gran_s_funeral/}}</ref> ''[[The Washington Post]]'' noted that by the next day the view count was above 900,000.<ref name="washingtonpost">{{cite news|work=[[The Washington Post]]|publisher=[[The Washington Post Company]]; Style Blog|accessdate=11 November 2014|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/style-blog/wp/2014/11/11/doctor-who-actor-peter-capaldi-records-moving-tribute-for-grieving-child/|title='Doctor Who' actor Peter Capaldi records moving tribute for grieving child|first=Thomas|last=Johnson}}</ref> Multiple publications observed that Capaldi's message had become a viral video.<ref name="bbccomforts" /><ref name="bbcmundo" /><ref name="timedwards">{{cite news|via=[[Westlaw]]|work=[[The Week]]|title=Doctor Who video for bereaved boy|date=10 November 2014|first=Tim|last=Edwards|location=United Kingdom|url=http://www.theweek.co.uk/daily-briefing/61256/ten-things-you-need-to-know-today-monday-10-nov-2014|accessdate=11 November 2014|archivedate=11 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111193031/http://www.theweek.co.uk/daily-briefing/61256/ten-things-you-need-to-know-today-monday-10-nov-2014}}</ref> ''[[ITV News]]'' called online reaction to the video "a worldwide phenomenon".<ref name="worldwidephenomenon">{{cite news|work=[[ITV News]]|accessdate=14 November 2014|date=10 November 2014|url=http://www.itv.com/news/meridian/update/2014-11-10/dr-who-sends-message-to-southampton-boy/|title=A message through time|archivedate=11 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111042416/http://www.itv.com/news/meridian/update/2014-11-10/dr-who-sends-message-to-southampton-boy/|last=Pate|first=Andrew|quote=Dr Who, the time travelling superhero, has sent a personal message to a boy from Southampton who has lost his Grandma. And the video has now become a worldwide phenomenon.}}</ref>

''[[The Guardian]]'' called the recording by Capaldi, "a heartwarming video message".<ref name="rawlinson" /> CNN characterized the video similarly,<ref name="grinberg" /> as did ''[[Digital Spy]]'',<ref name="finbow" /> ''ITV News'',<Ref>{{cite news|work=[[ITV News]]|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2014-11-09/peter-capaldi-sends-heartwarming-message-to-grieving-autistic-boy/|accessdate=10 November 2014|title=Peter Capaldi sends heartwarming message to grieving autistic boy|date=9 November 2014|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110222317/http://www.itv.com/news/2014-11-09/peter-capaldi-sends-heartwarming-message-to-grieving-autistic-boy/}}</ref> ''[[TV 3 (Ireland)|TV 3]]'';<ref>{{cite news|work=[[TV 3 (Ireland)|TV 3]]|location=[[Ireland]]|url=http://www.tv3.ie/3e/thread_article?threadid=944|accessdate=10 November 2014|title=Doctor Who records a sweet message for grieving boy|date=8 November 2014|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110222549/http://www.tv3.ie/3e/thread_article?threadid=944}}</ref> and other publications in [[Spanish language|Spanish]],<ref name="lavanguardia">{{cite news|work=[[La Vanguardia]]|language=[[Spanish language|Spanish]]|title=El v<U+00ED>deo que el actor de 'Doctor Who' manda a un ni<U+00F1>o con autismo|date=12 November 2014|accessdate=14 November 2014|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/series/personajes/20141112/54419221980/autista-doctor-who-video-nino-serie.html|publisher= La Vanguardia Ediciones S.L.|location=[[Barcelona]]|quote=Una bonita historia que demuestra lo feliz que se puede hacer a alguien con un peque<U+00F1>o gesto.}}</ref><Ref name="bbcmundo" /> and [[Dutch language|Dutch]].<ref name="deredactie" /> Spanish language newspaper ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' based in [[Barcelona]] wrote that Capaldi's video was an example of bringing joy into someone's life through a small act.<ref name="lavanguardia" /> ''The Washington Post'' called it a "moving tribute".<ref name="washingtonpost" /> ''[[The Daily Dot]]'' called the video inspirational.<ref name="aaronsankin">{{cite news|accessdate=11 November 2014|url=http://www.dailydot.com/geek/peter-capaldi-doctor-who-video-autistic-boy-ross-goddall/|archivedate=11 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111193300/http://www.dailydot.com/geek/peter-capaldi-doctor-who-video-autistic-boy-ross-goddall/|via=[[Westlaw]]|work=[[The Daily Dot]]|title='Doctor Who' actor sends inspiring video message to grieving autistic boy|first=Aaron|last=Sankin|date=9 November 2014}}</ref> ''[[The Independent]]'' wrote: "Peter Capaldi's ''Doctor Who'' may be one of the more sinister incarnations of the much-loved TV character British television has seen. But the actor never-the-less showed his softer side when he sent this heart-warming YouTube message".<ref name="selby">{{cite news|work=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=10 November 2014|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/peter-capaldi-sends-heartwarming-youtube-message-to-nineyearold-autistic-boy-learning-to-cope-with-grief-9849468.html|title=Peter Capaldi sends heart-warming YouTube message to autistic boy learning to cope with grief|last=Selby|first=Jenn|date=9 November 2014|archivedate=9 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109135233/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/peter-capaldi-sends-heartwarming-youtube-message-to-nineyearold-autistic-boy-learning-to-cope-with-grief-9849468.html}}</ref> ''[[MTV]]'' favorably covered the video: "Scottish actor Peter Capaldi is not only one of the best doctors to ever exist on 'Doctor Who'&nbsp;... he's also a super awesome human being".<ref name="mtv">{{cite news|first=Madeline|last=Roth|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1991733/peter-capaldi-dr-who-grieving-boy-video/|accessdate=10 November 2014|title=Watch Peter Capaldi Channel His <U+2018>Doctor Who<U+2019> Character To Help A Grieving Boy|date=8 November 2014|archivedate=10 November 2014|work=[[MTV]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110202955/http://www.mtv.com/news/1991733/peter-capaldi-dr-who-grieving-boy-video/}}</ref> ''MTV'' concluded, "Is there anything in the world cuter than this?!"<ref name="mtv" /> 

''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' described the video as a "touching message" to a "grieving boy".<ref name="alicevincent" /> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' observed: "When the Time Lord isn't busy preventing the destruction of the universe, he's also doing what he can to lift spirits."<ref name="hollywoodreporter">{{cite news|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|title=Watch 'Doctor Who' Star Peter Capaldi Channel the Time Lord in Video for Grieving Boy|first=Ryan |last=Gajewski|date=8 November 2014|accessdate=10 November 2014|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/watch-doctor-who-star-peter-747673|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110204800/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/watch-doctor-who-star-peter-747673}}</ref> ''[[Daily Mirror]]'' positively reviewed the video, writing: "Doctor Who star Peter Capaldi has demonstrated exactly why he is a hero to millions across the globe by sending a young boy who recently lost his grandmother a personal video message of support."<ref name="mirror">{{cite news|first=Rob|last=Leigh|work=[[Daily Mirror]]|accessdate=10 November 2014|url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/watch-doctor-who-hero-peter-4589677|date=7 November 2014|title=Watch Doctor Who hero Peter Capaldi offer 9-year-old autistic boy soothing words of comfort|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109134428/http://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/watch-doctor-who-hero-peter-4589677|archivedate=9 November 2014}}</ref> ''[[Hollywood Life]]'' admitted: "We shed a bunch of happy tears after listening to that message."<Ref name="hollywoodlife">{{cite news|work=[[Hollywood Life]]|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2014/11/08/peter-capaldi-doctor-who-video-autistic-boy-nanny-dies/|accessdate=10 November 2014|title=Peter Capaldi: <U+2018>Doctor Who' Star Sends Moving Video To Grieving Boy, 9|date=8 November 2014|first=Jordyn|last=Shaffer|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110210444/http://hollywoodlife.com/2014/11/08/peter-capaldi-doctor-who-video-autistic-boy-nanny-dies/}}</ref> Their review concluded, "Peter clearly applied the show's exploration of loss and death to Thomas' own grief. We not only think this is incredibly sweet, but it's also is very powerful!"<ref name="hollywoodlife" /> 

''[[International Business Times]]'' reported: "It was a short and simple message, but one that has had a profound impact on the little boy."<ref name="ibt" /> ''International Business Times'' noted in a follow-up piece that Capaldi's video was featured in headlines of multiple newspapers.<ref>{{cite news|work=[[International Business Times]]|accessdate=18 November 2014|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/doctor-who-star-peter-capaldi-confirmed-season-9-10-will-jenna-louise-coleman-return-1724991|title='Doctor Who' Star Peter Capaldi Confirmed For Season 9 And 10; Will Jenna-Louise Coleman Return?|date=17 November 2014|first=Tyler|last=McCarthy|archivedate=18 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141118005723/http://www.ibtimes.com/doctor-who-star-peter-capaldi-confirmed-season-9-10-will-jenna-louise-coleman-return-1724991}}</ref> ''[[BT Group|BT]]'' commented: "Capaldi<U+2019>s tenure in the Tardis has received mainly positive reviews so far, but this unique performance may well be his most admirable adventure yet."<ref name="btgroup">{{cite news|work=[[BT Group|BT]]|accessdate=10 November 2014|url=https://tv.bt.com/entertainment/tv/tv-news/doctor-who-star-peter-capaldi-sends-heartwarming-video-message-to-grieving-autistic-boy-11363943048094|title=Doctor Who star Peter Capaldi sends heartwarming video message to grieving autistic boy|date=10 November 2014|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110214556/https://tv.bt.com/entertainment/tv/tv-news/doctor-who-star-peter-capaldi-sends-heartwarming-video-message-to-grieving-autistic-boy-11363943048094}}</ref> ''[[The Huffington Post]]'' wrote: "You could travel through time and space and never find a sweeter story."<ref name="huffington">{{cite news|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=10 November 2014|first=Bill|last=Bradley|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/11/08/peter-capaldi-message_n_6126378.html|title=Peter Capaldi's Heartfelt Message To Young Fan Transcends Time And Space|archivedate=9 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109112953/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/11/08/peter-capaldi-message_n_6126378.html|date=8 November 2014}}</ref> ''[[io9]]'' appreciated that Capaldi was using his celebrity status to effect positive impact: "It's always immensely sweet when actors who play iconic characters understand the power those characters have and wield them for good."<Ref name="io9">{{cite news|work=[[io9]]|title=Peter Capaldi Recorded This Message In Character To Help A Grieving Boy|accessdate=10 November 2014|first=Lauren|last=Davis|date=7 November 2014|archivedate=10 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110215356/http://io9.com/peter-capaldi-recorded-this-message-in-character-to-hel-1656158665|url=http://io9.com/peter-capaldi-recorded-this-message-in-character-to-hel-1656158665}}</ref> ''Digital Spy'' followed up on its earlier favorable coverage of Capaldi's video, and highlighted it as the number one entry among "7 awesome celebrity moments that will melt your heart".<ref>{{cite news|title=7 awesome celebrity moments that will melt your heart|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=17 November 2014|archivedate=17 November 2014|date=16 November 2014|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/celebrity/feature/a610448/7-awesome-celebrity-moments-that-will-melt-your-heart.html|first=Frances|last=Taylor|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141117173927/http://www.digitalspy.com/celebrity/feature/a610448/7-awesome-celebrity-moments-that-will-melt-your-heart.html}}</ref>

''[[South Wales Evening Post]]'' noted Capaldi had previously appeared in a brief video as himself congratulating a bride on her wedding, writing: "and now he's gone one better".<ref name="southwales">{{cite news|work=[[South Wales Evening Post]]|accessdate=11 November 2014|date=7 November 2014|url=http://www.southwales-eveningpost.co.uk/VIDEO-Doctor-star-Peter-Capaldi-sends/story-24465933-detail/story.html|title=VIDEO: Doctor Who star Peter Capaldi sends heartwarming message to autistic boy mourning nanny|archivedate=11 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111173426/http://www.southwales-eveningpost.co.uk/VIDEO-Doctor-star-Peter-Capaldi-sends/story-24465933-detail/story.html|first=Ruth|last=Dawson}}</ref> ''[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]'' commented favorably: "Just when you thought Peter Capaldi couldn<U+2019>t possibly get any cooler, he<U+2019>s gone and outdone himself with this video."<ref name="westbrook">{{cite news|first=Caroline|last=Westbrook|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|title=Peter Capaldi becomes even more awesome as he records special message for autistic boy mourning his nanny|url=http://metro.co.uk/2014/11/07/peter-capaldi-just-got-a-little-cooler-as-he-records-special-message-for-autistic-boy-mourning-his-nanny-4939799/|accessdate=11 November 2014|date=7 November 2014|archivedate=8 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108054243/http://metro.co.uk/2014/11/07/peter-capaldi-just-got-a-little-cooler-as-he-records-special-message-for-autistic-boy-mourning-his-nanny-4939799/}}</ref> After the ''[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Scottish Daily Record]]'' reported on the video,<ref name="scottishdailyrecord" /> they followed up the next day noting several readers wrote the paper to express their gratitude to Capaldi.<ref name="dailyrecordp33">{{cite news|date=11 November 2014|page=33|via=[[InfoTrac]]|title=@dailyrecord|work=[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Scottish Daily Record]]|publisher=MGN Ltd. Scottish Daily Record & Sunday Mail Ltd|location=[[Scotland]]}}</ref> One reader told the ''Daily Record'' he had [[Asperger syndrome]] along the [[autism spectrum]] and particularly understood Thomas Goodall's situation and therefore appreciated how the video from Capaldi was meaningful.<ref name="dailyrecordp33" /> Capaldi's actions received favorable coverage from the ''Autism Daily Newscast''.<ref name="autismdaily">{{cite news|work=Autism Daily Newscast|url=http://www.autismdailynewscast.com/peter-capaldi-sends-heartwarming-video-mesaage-to-young-autistic-boy-whose-grandmother-has-recently-died/18540/joworgan/|accessdate=14 November 2014|date=9 November 2014|first=Jo|last=Worgan|title=Peter Capaldi sends heartwarming video mesaage to young autistic boy whose grandmother has recently died|archivedate=14 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141114195247/http://www.autismdailynewscast.com/peter-capaldi-sends-heartwarming-video-mesaage-to-young-autistic-boy-whose-grandmother-has-recently-died/18540/joworgan/}}</ref>

